Guare's other plays include 
               Rich and Famous
             (1974); 
               Landscape of the Body
            , for which he also wrote the songs (1977); 
               Marco Polo Sings a Solo
             (1977); 
               Bosoms and Neglect
             (1979); 
               Lydie Breeze
             (1982); 
               Gardenia
             (1982); 
               The Race to Urga
             (1986); 
               Women and Water
             (1990);
               Four Baboons Adoring the Sun
             (1992); 
               Lake Hollywood
             (1999); 
               Chaucer in Rome
            , sequel to 
               The House of Blue Leaves
             (2001); and 
               A Few Stout Individuals
             (2002). He also wrote the screenplay for Louis Malle's film 
               Atlantic City
             (1980), for which he was nominated for an Oscar.
